The paper deals with information theoretic secret key agreement and secure function computation, which are topics related to information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves interactive communication and multiparty computation, which are topics related to computer networks and distributed systems, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper discusses the feasibility of secure computation, which is a topic related to privacy and data protection, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible sub-category.
